{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "2d1dca7b-86dd-4df9-aed3-5fcc427283c2", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "3. Human Resources Policies", "section": "3.3 Compensation, Payroll & Overtime", "subsection": "3.3.5 Payroll Administration", "raw_content": "NexaCorp processes payroll on a semi-monthly basis (on the 15th and last business day of each month for salaried employees). Hourly employees are paid bi-weekly. Direct deposit is mandatory for all US employees. Employees must maintain current bank account information in the HRIS self-service portal. NexaCorp is not responsible for delays caused by employee-provided incorrect banking information. All changes to bank account details must be verified through a two-step authentication process and approved by HR Operations within 3 business days. This safeguard exists to prevent payroll fraud and social engineering attacks.", "type": "text", "text": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.3 Compensation, Payroll & Overtime\n            Subsection: 3.3.5 Payroll Administration\n            NexaCorp processes payroll on a semi-monthly basis (on the 15th and last business day of each month for salaried employees). Hourly employees are paid bi-weekly. Direct deposit is mandatory for all US employees. Employees must maintain current bank account information in the HRIS self-service portal. NexaCorp is not responsible for delays caused by employee-provided incorrect banking information. All changes to bank account details must be verified through a two-step authentication process and approved by HR Operations within 3 business days. This safeguard exists to prevent payroll fraud and social engineering attacks."}, "page_content": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.3 Compensation, Payroll & Overtime\n            Subsection: 3.3.5 Payroll Administration\n            NexaCorp processes payroll on a semi-monthly basis (on the 15th and last business day of each month for salaried employees). Hourly employees are paid bi-weekly. Direct deposit is mandatory for all US employees. Employees must maintain current bank account information in the HRIS self-service portal. NexaCorp is not responsible for delays caused by employee-provided incorrect banking information. All changes to bank account details must be verified through a two-step authentication process and approved by HR Operations within 3 business days. This safeguard exists to prevent payroll fraud and social engineering attacks.", "type": "Document"}}